## `group_vars/all/execution_environments.yml`

Never hardcode the image URL. Use `demo_execution_environment_image` variable,
`pull: missing`, and a `credential` for PAH authentication:

```yaml
controller_execution_environments:
  - name: "{{ demo_execution_environment_name }}"
    organization: "{{ demo_organization_name }}"
    image: "{{ demo_execution_environment_image }}"
    pull: missing
    credential: "{{ hub_registry_credential_name }}"
```

---

## `demo_variables.yml.example` — required EE variables

**This rule is the source of truth for these three variables** — `artifact--demo-variables.mdc`
cross-references this section instead of restating the values. Add them in the demo identity
section, immediately after `demo_execution_environment_name`:

```yaml
demo_execution_environment_image: CHANGE_ME/ee-<slug>:latest
hub_registry_credential_name: "PAH Container Registry - <Demo Title>"
hub_registry_host: "{{ aap_hostname | regex_replace('^https?://', '') | regex_replace('/$', '') }}"
```

### `hub_registry_credential_name` must be globally unique across artifacts (mandatory)

Never use the bare literal `PAH Container Registry` — suffix it with the artifact's title
(`<Demo Title>` above; match the wording used for `demo_project_name`), the same way
`demo_organization_name` and `demo_inventory_name` must be unique per
`artifact--demo-variables.mdc`. This is not a cosmetic preference: it works around a real
bug surface in `ansible.controller.execution_environment`. That module resolves its
`credential:` parameter with `module.resolve_name_to_id('credentials', credential)`, which
calls `GET /api/controller/v2/credentials/?name=<name>` **with no organization filter**.
`ansible.controller.credential` itself creates the credential correctly scoped to
`demo_organization_name`, so this never fails while only one artifact using the generic
name is deployed — but the moment a second artifact (in its own Organization, as required)
also creates a credential named `PAH Container Registry`, every subsequent `aap_config.yml`
run for either artifact fails with:

```
Request to /api/controller/v2/credentials/?name=PAH+Container+Registry returned 2 items, expected 1
```

Verify uniqueness against every sibling artifact before shipping, using the same pattern as
the org/inventory check in `artifact--demo-variables.mdc`:

```bash
grep -rn "hub_registry_credential_name:" \
  artifacts/demos/*/group_vars/all/demo_variables.yml.example
```

---

## `credentials.yml` — required PAH registry credential

Add this credential so Controller can pull the EE image from PAH:

```yaml
  - name: "{{ hub_registry_credential_name }}"
    organization: "{{ demo_organization_name }}"
    credential_type: Container Registry
    inputs:
      host: "{{ hub_registry_host }}"
      username: "{{ aap_username }}"
      password: "{{ aap_password }}"
      verify_ssl: false
    no_log: "{{ demo_no_log | default(true) }}"
```

---

## `docs/setup.md` — required build instructions

Step 3 must include login, build, and push with `--tls-verify=false`:

```bash
ansible-builder build \
  -f context/execution-environment.yml \
  -t <PAH-HOST>/ee-<slug>:latest \
  --container-runtime podman

podman login <PAH-HOST> --tls-verify=false

podman push <PAH-HOST>/ee-<slug>:latest --tls-verify=false
```

Set `demo_execution_environment_image: <PAH-HOST>/ee-<slug>:latest` in
`demo_variables.yml` before running `aap_config.yml`.
